obo:RO_0002333  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_900  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" , "Rationale: The authors use super-resolved tracking of a tagged Neurexin-1beta in live cultured hippocampal neurons. The results show that Neurexin-1beta sorts to presynaptic sites (Fig. 1), where it forms 1 to 2 nanoclusters per terminal while a dispersed population is additionally present in terminals (Fig. 1, 2, 3).. Experimental description: The neurexin-1beta construct was a gift from Alice Ting and cloned from mouse, see D. S. Liu et al., \"Imaging trans-cellular neurexin-neuroligin interactions by enzymatic probe ligation,\" Plos One 8(2), e52823 (2013).\n\n27/6/2017 Pim\n- Expert contacted authors on species of neurexin 1beta overexpression construct. Answer was:\n\"Hi Thomas, Thank you for selecting our paper. Yes we got this construct from Alice Ting and it should be a mouse sequence. best, ingrid\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3670-7863" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0912-1514" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_900" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

